story.text: I travel a lot. A large contributing factor to my excessive travel is tied to the house in Nye. I am in love with Nye, with the hill, and to a lesser extent, to the house I built. My mother wants to sell that house. To sell that land. It kills me. But it would lessen the demands that I travel so darn much. Perhaps I should let it go?
